var book = {
	"name": "Joshua",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death of Moses the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5853A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5853A\"></sup>servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses' <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5853B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5853B\"></sup>assistant,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Moses my servant is dead. Now therefore arise, go over this Jordan, you and all this people, into the land that I am giving to them, to the people of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5855C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5855C\"></sup>Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given to you, just as I promised to Moses.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5856D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5856D\"></sup>From the wilderness and this Lebanon as far as the great river, the river Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites to the Great Sea toward the going down of the sun shall be your territory.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5857E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5857E\"></sup>No man shall be able to stand before you all the days of your life. Just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5857F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5857F\"></sup>as I was with Moses, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5857G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5857G\"></sup>I will be with you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5857H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5857H\"></sup>I will not leave you or forsake you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5858I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5858I\"></sup>Be strong and courageous, for you shall cause this people to inherit the land that I swore to their fathers to give them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Only be strong and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5859J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5859J\"></sup>very courageous, being careful to do according to all the law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5859K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5859K\"></sup>that Moses my servant commanded you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5859L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5859L\"></sup>Do not turn from it to the right hand or to the left, that you may have good success wherever you go.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5860M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5860M\"></sup>you shall meditate on it day and night, so that you may be careful to do according to all that is written in it. For then you will make your way prosperous, and then you will have good success.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Have I not commanded you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5861N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5861N\"></sup>Be strong and courageous. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5861O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5861O\"></sup>Do not be frightened, and do not be dismayed, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is with you wherever you go.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Joshua commanded the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5862P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5862P\"></sup>officers of the people,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Pass through the midst of the camp and command the people, ‘Prepare your provisions, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5863Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5863Q\"></sup>within three days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5863R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5863R\"></sup>you are to pass over this Jordan to go in to take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving you to possess.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh Joshua said,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Remember the word that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5865S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5865S\"></sup>Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded you, saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is providing you a place of rest and will give you this land.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in the land that Moses gave you beyond the Jordan, but all the men of valor among you shall pass over armed before your brothers and shall help them,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5867T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5867T\"></sup>until the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives rest to your brothers as he has to you, and they also take possession of the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is giving them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5867U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5867U\"></sup>Then you shall return to the land of your possession and shall possess it, the land that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you beyond the Jordan toward the sunrise.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they answered Joshua, “All that you have commanded us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Just as we obeyed Moses in all things, so we will obey you. Only may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5869V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5869V\"></sup>be with you, as he was with Moses!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whoever rebels against your commandment and disobeys your words, whatever you command him, shall be put to death. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5870W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5870W\"></sup>Only be strong and courageous.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>And Joshua the son of Nun <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5871A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5871A\"></sup>sent two men secretly from Shittim as spies, saying, “Go, view the land, especially Jericho.” And they went and came into the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5871B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5871B\"></sup>a prostitute whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5871C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5871C\"></sup>Rahab and lodged there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And it was told to the king of Jericho, “Behold, men of Israel have come here tonight to search out the land.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king of Jericho sent to Rahab, saying, “Bring out the men who have come to you, who entered your house, for they have come to search out all the land.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the woman had taken the two men and hidden them. And she said, “True, the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when the gate was about to be closed at dark, the men went out. I do not know where the men went. Pursue them quickly, for you will overtake them.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But she had brought them up to the roof and hid them with the stalks of flax that she had laid in order on the roof.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the men pursued after them on the way to the Jordan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5877D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5877D\"></sup>as far as the fords. And the gate was shut as soon as the pursuers had gone out.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Before the men lay down, she came up to them on the roof",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and said to the men, “I know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5879E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5879E\"></sup>and that the fear of you has fallen upon us, and that all the inhabitants of the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5879F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5879F\"></sup>melt away before you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For we have heard how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5880G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5880G\"></sup>dried up the water of the Red Sea before you when you came out of Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5880H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5880H\"></sup>what you did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5880I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5880I\"></sup>Sihon and Og, whom you devoted to destruction.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5881J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5881J\"></sup>as soon as we heard it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5881K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5881K\"></sup>our hearts melted, and there was no spirit left in any man because of you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5881L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5881L\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, he is God in the heavens above and on the earth beneath.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now then, please swear to me by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that, as I have dealt kindly with you, you also will deal kindly with my father's house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5882M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5882M\"></sup>give me a sure sign",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>that you will save alive my father and mother, my brothers and sisters, and all who belong to them, and deliver our lives from death.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the men said to her, “Our life for yours even to death! If you do not tell this business of ours, then when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives us the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5884N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5884N\"></sup>we will deal kindly and faithfully with you.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5885O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5885O\"></sup>let them down by a rope through the window, for her house was built into the city wall, so that she lived in the wall.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And she said to them, “Go into the hills, or the pursuers will encounter you, and hide there three days until the pursuers have returned. Then afterward you may go your way.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The men said to her, “We will be guiltless with respect to this oath of yours that you have made us swear.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5888P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5888P\"></sup>Behold, when we come into the land, you shall tie this scarlet cord in the window through which you let us down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5888Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5888Q\"></sup>and you shall gather into your house your father and mother, your brothers, and all your father's household.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then if anyone goes out of the doors of your house into the street, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5889R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5889R\"></sup>his blood shall be on his own head, and we shall be guiltless. But if a hand is laid on anyone who is with you in the house, his blood shall be on our head.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5890S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5890S\"></sup>tell this business of ours, then we shall be guiltless with respect to your oath that you have made us swear.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And she said, “According to your words, so be it.” Then she sent them away, and they departed. And she tied the scarlet cord in the window.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>They departed and went into the hills and remained there three days until the pursuers returned, and the pursuers searched all along the way and found nothing.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the two men returned. They came down from the hills and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5893T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5893T\"></sup>passed over and came to Joshua the son of Nun, and they told him all that had happened to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And they said to Joshua, “Truly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5894U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5894U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given all the land into our hands. And also, all the inhabitants of the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5894V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5894V\"></sup>melt away because of us.”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Then Joshua rose early in the morning and they set out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5895A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5895A\"></sup>from Shittim. And they came to the Jordan, he and all the people of Israel, and lodged there before they passed over.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5896B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5896B\"></sup>At the end of three days the officers went through the camp",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and commanded the people, “As soon as you see the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God being carried by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5897C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5897C\"></sup>the Levitical priests, then you shall set out from your place and follow it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5898D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5898D\"></sup>Yet there shall be a distance between you and it, about 2,000 cubits in length. Do not come near it, in order that you may know the way you shall go, for you have not passed this way before.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Joshua said to the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5899E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5899E\"></sup>“Consecrate yourselves, for tomorrow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do wonders among you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Joshua said to the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5900F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5900F\"></sup>“Take up the ark of the covenant and pass on before the people.” So they took up the ark of the covenant and went before the people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Today I will begin to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5901G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5901G\"></sup>exalt you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5901H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5901H\"></sup>as I was with Moses, so I will be with you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And as for you, command <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5902I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5902I\"></sup>the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, ‘When you come to the brink of the waters of the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5902J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5902J\"></sup>you shall stand still in the Jordan.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joshua said to the people of Israel, “Come here and listen to the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Joshua said, “Here is how you shall know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5904K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5904K\"></sup>the living God is among you and that he will without fail <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5904L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5904L\"></sup>drive out from before you the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Hivites, the Perizzites, the Girgashites, the Amorites, and the Jebusites.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Behold, the ark of the covenant of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5905M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5905M\"></sup>the Lord of all the earth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5905N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5905N\"></sup>is passing over before you into the Jordan.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5906O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5906O\"></sup>take twelve men from the tribes of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5906P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5906P\"></sup>from each tribe a man.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5907Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5907Q\"></sup>when the soles of the feet of the priests bearing the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5907R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5907R\"></sup>the Lord of all the earth, shall rest in the waters of the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan shall be cut off from flowing, and the waters coming down from above shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5907S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5907S\"></sup>stand in one heap.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So when the people set out from their tents to pass over the Jordan with the priests bearing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5908T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5908T\"></sup>the ark of the covenant before the people,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and as soon as those bearing the ark had come as far as the Jordan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5909U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5909U\"></sup>the feet of the priests bearing the ark were dipped in the brink of the water (now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5909V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5909V\"></sup>the Jordan overflows all its banks <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5909W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5909W\"></sup>throughout the time of harvest),",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the waters coming down from above stood and rose up in a heap very far away, at Adam, the city that is beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5910X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5910X\"></sup>Zarethan, and those flowing down toward the Sea of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5910Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5910Y\"></sup>the Arabah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5910Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5910Z\"></sup>the Salt Sea, were completely cut off. And the people passed over opposite Jericho.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the priests bearing the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stood firmly on dry ground in the midst of the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5911AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5911AA\"></sup>and all Israel was passing over on dry ground until all the nation finished passing over the Jordan."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When all the nation had finished passing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5912A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5912A\"></sup>over the Jordan, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5913B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5913B\"></sup>“Take twelve men from the people, from each tribe a man,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and command them, saying, ‘Take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5914C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5914C\"></sup>twelve stones from here out of the midst of the Jordan, from the very place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5914D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5914D\"></sup>where the priests' feet stood firmly, and bring them over with you and lay them down in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5914E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5914E\"></sup>the place where you lodge tonight.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Joshua called the twelve men from the people of Israel, whom he had appointed, a man from each tribe.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Joshua said to them, “Pass on before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God into the midst of the Jordan, and take up each of you a stone upon his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the people of Israel,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>that this may be a sign among you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5917F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5917F\"></sup>When your children ask in time to come, ‘What do those stones mean to you?’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then you shall tell them that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5918G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5918G\"></sup>the waters of the Jordan were cut off before the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. When it passed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. So these stones shall be to the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5918H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5918H\"></sup>a memorial forever.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the people of Israel did just as Joshua commanded and took up twelve stones out of the midst of the Jordan, according to the number of the tribes of the people of Israel, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told Joshua. And they carried them over with them to the place where they lodged and laid them down there.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joshua set up twelve stones in the midst of the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5920I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5920I\"></sup>in the place where the feet of the priests bearing the ark of the covenant had stood; and they are there to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the priests bearing the ark stood in the midst of the Jordan until everything was finished that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Joshua to tell the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua.The people passed over in haste.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And when all the people had finished passing over, the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the priests passed over before the people.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5923J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5923J\"></sup>passed over armed before the people of Israel, as Moses had told them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>About 40,000 ready for war passed over before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for battle, to the plains of Jericho.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>On that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5925K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5925K\"></sup>exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel, and they stood in awe of him just as they had stood in awe of Moses, all the days of his life.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Command the priests bearing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5927L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5927L\"></sup>the ark of the testimony to come up out of the Jordan.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Joshua commanded the priests, “Come up out of the Jordan.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when the priests bearing the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came up from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests' feet were lifted up on dry ground, the waters of the Jordan returned to their place and overflowed all its banks, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5929M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5929M\"></sup>as before.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The people came up out of the Jordan on the tenth day of the first month, and they encamped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5930N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5930N\"></sup>Gilgal on the east border of Jericho.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5931O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5931O\"></sup>those twelve stones, which they took out of the Jordan, Joshua set up at Gilgal.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he said to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5932P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5932P\"></sup>“When your children ask their fathers in times to come, ‘What do these stones mean?’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>then you shall let your children know, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5933Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5933Q\"></sup>‘Israel passed over this Jordan on dry ground.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God dried up the waters of the Jordan for you until you passed over, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God did to the Red Sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5934R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5934R\"></sup>which he dried up for us until we passed over,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5935S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5935S\"></sup>so that all the peoples of the earth may know that the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5935T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5935T\"></sup>mighty, that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5935U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5935U\"></sup>fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God forever.”"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>As soon as all the kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan to the west, and all the kings of the Canaanites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5936A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5936A\"></sup>who were by the sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5936B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5936B\"></sup>heard that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had dried up the waters of the Jordan for the people of Israel until they had crossed over, their hearts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5936C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5936C\"></sup>melted and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5936D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5936D\"></sup>there was no longer any spirit in them because of the people of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At that time the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5937E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5937E\"></sup>flint knives and circumcise the sons of Israel a second time.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua made flint knives and circumcised the sons of Israel at Gibeath-haaraloth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And this is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5939F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5939F\"></sup>all the males of the people who came out of Egypt, all the men of war, had died in the wilderness on the way after they had come out of Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Though all the people who came out had been circumcised, yet all the people who were born on the way in the wilderness after they had come out of Egypt had not been circumcised.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the people of Israel walked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5941G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5941G\"></sup>forty years in the wilderness, until all the nation, the men of war who came out of Egypt, perished, because they did not obey the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5941H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5941H\"></sup>swore to them that he would not let them see the land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had sworn to their fathers to give to us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5941I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5941I\"></sup>a land flowing with milk and honey.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5942J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5942J\"></sup>their children, whom he raised up in their place, that Joshua circumcised. For they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised on the way.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the circumcising of the whole nation was finished, they remained in their places in the camp until they were healed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Today I have rolled away the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5944K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5944K\"></sup>reproach of Egypt from you.” And so the name of that place is called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5944L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5944L\"></sup>Gilgal to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>While the people of Israel were encamped at Gilgal, they kept the Passover <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5945M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5945M\"></sup>on the fourteenth day of the month in the evening on the plains of Jericho.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the day after the Passover, on that very day, they ate of the produce of the land, unleavened cakes and parched grain.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5947N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5947N\"></sup>the manna ceased the day after they ate of the produce of the land. And there was no longer manna for the people of Israel, but they ate of the fruit of the land of Canaan that year.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Joshua was by Jericho, he lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5948O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5948O\"></sup>a man was standing before him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5948P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5948P\"></sup>with his drawn sword in his hand. And Joshua went to him and said to him, “Are you for us, or for our adversaries?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he said, “No; but I am the commander of the army of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Now I have come.” And Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5949Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5949Q\"></sup>fell on his face to the earth and worshiped and said to him, “What does my lord say to his servant?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the commander of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s army said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5950R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5950R\"></sup>“Take off your sandals from your feet, for the place where you are standing is holy.” And Joshua did so."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now Jericho was shut up inside and outside because of the people of Israel. None went out, and none came in.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5952A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5952A\"></sup>I have given Jericho into your hand, with its king and mighty men of valor.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall march around the city, all the men of war going around the city once. Thus shall you do for six days.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Seven priests shall bear seven <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5954B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5954B\"></sup>trumpets of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5954C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5954C\"></sup>rams' horns before the ark. On the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5954D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5954D\"></sup>the priests shall blow the trumpets.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when they make a long blast with the ram's horn, when you hear the sound of the trumpet, then all the people shall shout with a great shout, and the wall of the city will fall down flat, and the people shall go up, everyone straight before him.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Joshua the son of Nun called the priests and said to them, “Take up the ark of the covenant and let seven priests bear seven trumpets of rams' horns before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he said to the people, “Go forward. March around the city and let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5957E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5957E\"></sup>the armed men pass on before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And just as Joshua had commanded the people, the seven priests bearing the seven trumpets of rams' horns before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went forward, blowing the trumpets, with the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> following them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The armed men were walking before the priests who were blowing the trumpets, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5959F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5959F\"></sup>rear guard was walking after the ark, while the trumpets blew continually.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Joshua commanded the people, “You shall not shout or make your voice heard, neither shall any word go out of your mouth, until the day I tell you to shout. Then you shall shout.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So he caused the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to circle the city, going about it once. And they came into the camp and spent the night in the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joshua rose early in the morning, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5962G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5962G\"></sup>the priests took up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the seven priests bearing the seven trumpets of rams' horns before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> walked on, and they blew the trumpets continually. And the armed men were walking before them, and the rear guard was walking after the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while the trumpets blew continually.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the second day they marched around the city once, and returned into the camp. So they did for six days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the seventh day they rose early, at the dawn of day, and marched around the city in the same manner seven times. It was only on that day that they marched around the city seven times.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And at the seventh time, when the priests had blown the trumpets, Joshua said to the people, “Shout, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you the city.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the city and all that is within it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5967H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5967H\"></sup>devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for destruction. Only Rahab the prostitute and all who are with her in her house shall live, because she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5967I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5967I\"></sup>hid the messengers whom we sent.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But you, keep yourselves from the things devoted to destruction, lest when you have devoted them you take any of the devoted things and make the camp of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5968J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5968J\"></sup>a thing for destruction and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5968K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5968K\"></sup>bring trouble upon it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But all silver and gold, and every vessel of bronze and iron, are holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they shall go into the treasury of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So the people shouted, and the trumpets were blown. As soon as the people heard the sound of the trumpet, the people shouted a great shout, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5970L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5970L\"></sup>the wall fell down flat, so that the people went up into the city, every man straight before him, and they captured the city.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5971M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5971M\"></sup>devoted all in the city to destruction, both men and women, young and old, oxen, sheep, and donkeys, with the edge of the sword.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But to the two men who had spied out the land, Joshua said, “Go into the prostitute's house and bring out from there the woman and all who belong to her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5972N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5972N\"></sup>as you swore to her.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the young men who had been spies went in and brought out Rahab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5973O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5973O\"></sup>her father and mother and brothers and all who belonged to her. And they brought all her relatives and put them outside the camp of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And they burned the city with fire, and everything in it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5974P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5974P\"></sup>Only the silver and gold, and the vessels of bronze and of iron, they put into the treasury of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Rahab the prostitute and her father's household and all who belonged to her, Joshua saved alive. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5975Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5975Q\"></sup>she has lived in Israel to this day, because she hid the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joshua laid an oath on them at that time, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5976R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5976R\"></sup>“Cursed before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be the man who rises up and rebuilds this city, Jericho.“At the cost of his firstborn shall helay its foundation,and at the cost of his youngest sonshall he set up its gates.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5977S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5977S\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joshua, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5977T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5977T\"></sup>his fame was in all the land."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>But the people of Israel broke faith in regard to the devoted things, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5978A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5978A\"></sup>Achan the son of Carmi, son of Zabdi, son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, took some of the devoted things. And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against the people of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5979B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5979B\"></sup>Beth-aven, east of Bethel, and said to them, “Go up and spy out the land.” And the men went up and spied out Ai.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they returned to Joshua and said to him, “Do not have all the people go up, but let about two or three thousand men go up and attack Ai. Do not make the whole people toil up there, for they are few.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So about three thousand men went up there from the people. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5981C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5981C\"></sup>they fled before the men of Ai,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and the men of Ai killed about thirty-six of their men and chased them before the gate as far as Shebarim and struck them at the descent. And the hearts of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5982D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5982D\"></sup>melted and became as water.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5983E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5983E\"></sup>tore his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5983F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5983F\"></sup>fell to the earth on his face before the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> until the evening, he and the elders of Israel. And they put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5983G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5983G\"></sup>dust on their heads.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Joshua said, “Alas, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5984H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5984H\"></sup>why have you brought this people over the Jordan at all, to give us into the hands of the Amorites, to destroy us? Would that we had been content to dwell beyond the Jordan!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>O Lord, what can I say, when Israel has turned their backs before their enemies!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear of it and will surround us and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5986I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5986I\"></sup>cut off our name from the earth. And what will you do for your great name?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, “Get up! Why have you fallen on your face?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Israel has sinned; they have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5988J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5988J\"></sup>transgressed my covenant that I commanded them; they have taken some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5988K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5988K\"></sup>devoted things; they have stolen and lied and put them among their own belongings.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5989L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5989L\"></sup>Therefore the people of Israel cannot stand before their enemies. They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5989M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5989M\"></sup>turn their backs before their enemies, because they have become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5989N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5989N\"></sup>devoted for destruction. I will be with you no more, unless you destroy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5989O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5989O\"></sup>the devoted things from among you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Get up! Consecrate the people and say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5990P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5990P\"></sup>‘Consecrate yourselves for tomorrow; for thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of Israel, “There are devoted things in your midst, O Israel. You cannot stand before your enemies until you take away the devoted things from among you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the morning therefore you shall be brought near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5991Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5991Q\"></sup>by your tribes. And the tribe that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes by lot shall come near by clans. And the clan that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes shall come near by households. And the household that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> takes shall come near man by man.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5992R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5992R\"></sup>And he who is taken with the devoted things shall be burned with fire, he and all that he has, because he has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5992S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5992S\"></sup>transgressed the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and because he has done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5992T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5992T\"></sup>an outrageous thing in Israel.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Joshua rose early in the morning and brought Israel near tribe by tribe, and the tribe of Judah was taken.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he brought near the clans of Judah, and the clan of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5994U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5994U\"></sup>Zerahites was taken. And he brought near the clan of the Zerahites man by man, and Zabdi was taken.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he brought near his household man by man, and Achan the son of Carmi, son of Zabdi, son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was taken.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Joshua said to Achan, “My son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5996V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5996V\"></sup>give glory to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5996W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5996W\"></sup>give praise to him. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5996X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5996X\"></sup>tell me now what you have done; do not hide it from me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Achan answered Joshua, “Truly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-5997Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-5997Y\"></sup>I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, and this is what I did:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>when I saw among the spoil a beautiful cloak from Shinar, and 200 shekels of silver, and a bar of gold weighing 50 shekels, then I coveted them and took them. And see, they are hidden in the earth inside my tent, with the silver underneath.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and behold, it was hidden in his tent with the silver underneath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they took them out of the tent and brought them to Joshua and to all the people of Israel. And they laid them down before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Joshua and all Israel with him took Achan the son of Zerah, and the silver and the cloak and the bar of gold, and his sons and daughters and his oxen and donkeys and sheep and his tent and all that he had. And they brought them up to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6001Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6001Z\"></sup>Valley of Achor.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Joshua said, “Why did you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6002AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6002AA\"></sup>bring trouble on us? The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brings trouble on you today.” And all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6002AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6002AB\"></sup>stoned him with stones. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6002AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6002AC\"></sup>They burned them with fire and stoned them with stones.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they raised over him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6003AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6003AD\"></sup>a great heap of stones that remains to this day. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6003AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6003AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned from his burning anger. Therefore, to this day the name of that place is called the Valley of Achor."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6004A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6004A\"></sup>“Do not fear and do not be dismayed. Take all the fighting men with you, and arise, go up to Ai. See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6004B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6004B\"></sup>I have given into your hand the king of Ai, and his people, his city, and his land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And you shall do to Ai and its king as you did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6005C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6005C\"></sup>to Jericho and its king. Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6005D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6005D\"></sup>its spoil and its livestock you shall take as plunder for yourselves. Lay an ambush against the city, behind it.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua and all the fighting men arose to go up to Ai. And Joshua chose 30,000 mighty men of valor and sent them out by night.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he commanded them, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6007E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6007E\"></sup>you shall lie in ambush against the city, behind it. Do not go very far from the city, but all of you remain ready.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And I and all the people who are with me will approach the city. And when they come out against us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6008F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6008F\"></sup>just as before, we shall flee before them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they will come out after us, until we have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6009G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6009G\"></sup>drawn them away from the city. For they will say, ‘They are fleeing from us, just as before.’ So we will flee before them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then you shall rise up from the ambush and seize the city, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will give it into your hand.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And as soon as you have taken the city, you shall set the city on fire. You shall do according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6011H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6011H\"></sup>See, I have commanded you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Joshua sent them out. And they went to the place of ambush and lay between Bethel and Ai, to the west of Ai, but Joshua spent that night among the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Joshua arose early in the morning and mustered the people and went up, he and the elders of Israel, before the people to Ai.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6014I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6014I\"></sup>all the fighting men who were with him went up and drew near before the city and encamped on the north side of Ai, with a ravine between them and Ai.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He took about 5,000 men and set them in ambush between Bethel and Ai, to the west of the city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So they stationed the forces, the main encampment that was north of the city and its rear guard west of the city. But Joshua spent that night in the valley.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And as soon as the king of Ai saw this, he and all his people, the men of the city, hurried and went out early to the appointed place toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6017J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6017J\"></sup>the Arabah to meet Israel in battle. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6017K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6017K\"></sup>But he did not know that there was an ambush against him behind the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Joshua and all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6018L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6018L\"></sup>pretended to be beaten before them and fled in the direction of the wilderness.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So all the people who were in the city were called together to pursue them, and as they pursued Joshua they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6019M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6019M\"></sup>were drawn away from the city.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Not a man was left in Ai or Bethel who did not go out after Israel. They left the city open and pursued Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6021N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6021N\"></sup>“Stretch out the javelin that is in your hand toward Ai, for I will give it into your hand.” And Joshua stretched out the javelin that was in his hand toward the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the men in the ambush rose quickly out of their place, and as soon as he had stretched out his hand, they ran and entered the city and captured it. And they hurried to set the city on fire.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So when the men of Ai looked back, behold, the smoke of the city went up to heaven, and they had no power to flee this way or that, for the people who fled to the wilderness turned back against the pursuers.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had captured the city, and that the smoke of the city went up, then they turned back and struck down the men of Ai.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the others came out from the city against them, so they were in the midst of Israel, some on this side, and some on that side. And Israel struck them down, until there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6025O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6025O\"></sup>left none that survived or escaped.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But the king of Ai they took alive, and brought him near to Joshua.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Israel had finished killing all the inhabitants of Ai in the open wilderness where they pursued them, and all of them to the very last had fallen by the edge of the sword, all Israel returned to Ai and struck it down with the edge of the sword.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And all who fell that day, both men and women, were 12,000, all the people of Ai.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Joshua did not draw back his hand with which he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6029P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6029P\"></sup>stretched out the javelin until he had devoted all the inhabitants of Ai to destruction.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as their plunder, according to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6030Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6030Q\"></sup>commanded Joshua.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joshua burned Ai and made it forever a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6031R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6031R\"></sup>heap of ruins, as it is to this day.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6032S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6032S\"></sup>And he hanged the king of Ai on a tree until evening. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6032T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6032T\"></sup>And at sunset Joshua commanded, and they took his body down from the tree and threw it at the entrance of the gate of the city and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6032U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6032U\"></sup>raised over it a great heap of stones, which stands there to this day.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>At that time Joshua built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6033V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6033V\"></sup>on Mount Ebal,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>just as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded the people of Israel, as it is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, “an altar of uncut stones, upon which no man has wielded an iron tool.” And they offered on it burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sacrificed peace offerings.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And there, in the presence of the people of Israel, he wrote on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6035W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6035W\"></sup>the stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he had written.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And all Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6036X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6036X\"></sup>sojourner as well as native born, with their elders and officers and their judges, stood on opposite sides of the ark before the Levitical priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6036Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6036Y\"></sup>who carried the ark of the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, half of them in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front of Mount Ebal, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6036Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6036Z\"></sup>just as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded at the first, to bless the people of Israel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And afterward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6037AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6037AA\"></sup>he read all the words of the law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6037AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6037AB\"></sup>the blessing and the curse, according to all that is written in the Book of the Law.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>There was not a word of all that Moses commanded that Joshua did not read before all the assembly of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6038AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6038AC\"></sup>and the women, and the little ones, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6038AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6038AD\"></sup>the sojourners who lived among them."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>As soon as all the kings who were beyond the Jordan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6039A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6039A\"></sup>in the hill country and in the lowland all along the coast <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6039B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6039B\"></sup>of the Great Sea toward Lebanon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6039C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6039C\"></sup>the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, heard of this,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>they gathered together as one to fight against Joshua and Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But when the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6041D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6041D\"></sup>Gibeon heard what Joshua had done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6041E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6041E\"></sup>to Jericho and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6041F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6041F\"></sup>to Ai,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>they on their part acted with cunning and went and made ready provisions and took worn-out sacks for their donkeys, and wineskins, worn-out and torn and mended,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>with worn-out, patched sandals on their feet, and worn-out clothes. And all their provisions were dry and crumbly.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they went to Joshua in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6044G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6044G\"></sup>the camp at Gilgal and said to him and to the men of Israel, “We have come from a distant country, so now make a covenant with us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the men of Israel said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6045H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6045H\"></sup>the Hivites, “Perhaps you live among us; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6045I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6045I\"></sup>how can we make a covenant with you?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6046J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6046J\"></sup>“We are your servants.” And Joshua said to them, “Who are you? And where do you come from?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6047K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6047K\"></sup>“From a very distant country your servants have come, because of the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6047L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6047L\"></sup>For we have heard a report of him, and all that he did in Egypt,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6048M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6048M\"></sup>and all that he did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, to Sihon the king of Heshbon, and to Og king of Bashan, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6048N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6048N\"></sup>Ashtaroth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So our elders and all the inhabitants of our country said to us, ‘Take provisions in your hand for the journey and go to meet them and say to them, “We are your servants. Come now, make a covenant with us.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Here is our bread. It was still warm when we took it from our houses as our food for the journey on the day we set out to come to you, but now, behold, it is dry and crumbly.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These wineskins were new when we filled them, and behold, they have burst. And these garments and sandals of ours are worn out from the very long journey.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the men took some of their provisions, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6052O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6052O\"></sup>did not ask counsel from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6053P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6053P\"></sup>made peace with them and made a covenant with them, to let them live, and the leaders of the congregation swore to them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At the end of three days after they had made a covenant with them, they heard that they were their neighbors <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6054Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6054Q\"></sup>and that they lived among them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the people of Israel set out and reached their cities on the third day. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6055R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6055R\"></sup>Now their cities were Gibeon, Chephirah, Beeroth, and Kiriath-jearim.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the people of Israel did not attack them, because the leaders of the congregation had sworn to them by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel. Then all the congregation murmured against the leaders.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But all the leaders said to all the congregation, “We have sworn to them by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and now we may not touch them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>This we will do to them: let them live, lest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6058S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6058S\"></sup>wrath be upon us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6058T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6058T\"></sup>because of the oath that we swore to them.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the leaders said to them, “Let them live.” So they became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6059U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6059U\"></sup>cutters of wood and drawers of water for all the congregation, just as the leaders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6059V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6059V\"></sup>had said of them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joshua summoned them, and he said to them, “Why did you deceive us, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6060W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6060W\"></sup>‘We are very far from you,’ when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6060X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6060X\"></sup>you dwell among us?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now therefore you are cursed, and some of you shall never be anything but servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6061Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6061Y\"></sup>cutters of wood and drawers of water for the house of my God.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They answered Joshua, “Because it was told to your servants for a certainty that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6062Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6062Z\"></sup>commanded his servant Moses to give you all the land and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land from before you—so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6062AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6062AA\"></sup>we feared greatly for our lives because of you and did this thing.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And now, behold, we are in your hand. Whatever seems good and right in your sight to do to us, do it.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So he did this to them and delivered them out of the hand of the people of Israel, and they did not kill them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Joshua made them that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6065AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6065AB\"></sup>cutters of wood and drawers of water for the congregation and for the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6065AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6065AC\"></sup>in the place that he should choose."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>As soon as Adoni-zedek, king of Jerusalem, heard how Joshua had captured Ai and had devoted it to destruction, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6066A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6066A\"></sup>doing to Ai and its king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6066B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6066B\"></sup>as he had done to Jericho and its king, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6066C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6066C\"></sup>how the inhabitants of Gibeon had made peace with Israel and were among them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6067D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6067D\"></sup>he feared greatly, because Gibeon was a great city, like one of the royal cities, and because it was greater than Ai, and all its men were warriors.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Adoni-zedek king of Jerusalem sent to Hoham king of Hebron, to Piram king of Jarmuth, to Japhia king of Lachish, and to Debir king of Eglon, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Come up to me and help me, and let us strike Gibeon. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6069E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6069E\"></sup>it has made peace with Joshua and with the people of Israel.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6070F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6070F\"></sup>gathered their forces and went up with all their armies and encamped against Gibeon and made war against it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the men of Gibeon sent to Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6071G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6071G\"></sup>at the camp in Gilgal, saying, “Do not relax your hand from your servants. Come up to us quickly and save us and help us, for all the kings of the Amorites who dwell in the hill country are gathered against us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joshua went up from Gilgal, he and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6072H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6072H\"></sup>all the people of war with him, and all the mighty men of valor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6073I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6073I\"></sup>“Do not fear them, for I have given them into your hands. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6073J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6073J\"></sup>Not a man of them shall stand before you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Joshua came upon them suddenly, having marched up all night from Gilgal.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6075K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6075K\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> threw them into a panic before Israel, who struck them with a great blow at Gibeon and chased them by the way of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6075L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6075L\"></sup>the ascent of Beth-horon and struck them as far as Azekah and Makkedah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And as they fled before Israel, while they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6076M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6076M\"></sup>going down the ascent of Beth-horon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6076N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6076N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> threw down large stones from heaven on them as far as Azekah, and they died. There were more who died because of the hailstones than the sons of Israel killed with the sword.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>At that time Joshua spoke to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the day when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the Amorites over to the sons of Israel, and he said in the sight of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6077O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6077O\"></sup>“Sun, stand still at Gibeon,and moon, in the Valley of Aijalon.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the sun stood still, and the moon stopped,until the nation took vengeance on their enemies.Is this not written in the Book of Jashar? The sun stopped in the midst of heaven and did not hurry to set for about a whole day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6079P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6079P\"></sup>There has been no day like it before or since, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heeded the voice of a man, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6079Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6079Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fought for Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6080R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6080R\"></sup>Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These five kings fled and hid themselves in the cave at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6081S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6081S\"></sup>Makkedah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And it was told to Joshua, “The five kings have been found, hidden in the cave at Makkedah.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Joshua said, “Roll large stones against the mouth of the cave and set men by it to guard them,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>but do not stay there yourselves. Pursue your enemies; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6084T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6084T\"></sup>attack their rear guard. Do not let them enter their cities, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given them into your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Joshua and the sons of Israel had finished striking them with a great blow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6085U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6085U\"></sup>until they were wiped out, and when the remnant that remained of them had entered into the fortified cities,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then all the people returned safe to Joshua in the camp at Makkedah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6086V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6086V\"></sup>Not a man moved his tongue against any of the people of Israel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Joshua said, “Open the mouth of the cave and bring those five kings out to me from the cave.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they did so, and brought those five kings out to him from the cave, the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And when they brought those kings out to Joshua, Joshua summoned all the men of Israel and said to the chiefs of the men of war who had gone with him, “Come near; put your feet on the necks of these kings.” Then they came near and put their feet on their necks.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Joshua said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6090W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6090W\"></sup>“Do not be afraid or dismayed; be strong and courageous. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6090X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6090X\"></sup>For thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do to all your enemies against whom you fight.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And afterward Joshua struck them and put them to death, and he hanged them on five trees. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6091Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6091Y\"></sup>they hung on the trees until evening.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But at the time of the going down of the sun, Joshua commanded, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6092Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6092Z\"></sup>they took them down from the trees and threw them into the cave where they had hidden themselves, and they set large stones against the mouth of the cave, which remain to this very day.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>As for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6093AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6093AA\"></sup>Makkedah, Joshua captured it on that day and struck it, and its king, with the edge of the sword. He devoted to destruction every person in it; he left none remaining. And he did to the king of Makkedah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6093AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6093AB\"></sup>just as he had done to the king of Jericho.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Makkedah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6094AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6094AC\"></sup>Libnah and fought against Libnah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave it also and its king into the hand of Israel. And he struck it with the edge of the sword, and every person in it; he left none remaining in it. And he did to its king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6095AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6095AD\"></sup>as he had done to the king of Jericho.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Libnah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6096AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6096AE\"></sup>Lachish and laid siege to it and fought against it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Lachish into the hand of Israel, and he captured it on the second day and struck it with the edge of the sword, and every person in it, as he had done to Libnah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Horam king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6098AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6098AF\"></sup>Gezer came up to help Lachish. And Joshua struck him and his people, until he left none remaining.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Lachish to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6099AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6099AG\"></sup>Eglon. And they laid siege to it and fought against it.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And they captured it on that day, and struck it with the edge of the sword. And he devoted every person in it to destruction that day, as he had done to Lachish.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him went up from Eglon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6101AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6101AH\"></sup>Hebron. And they fought against it",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and captured it and struck it with the edge of the sword, and its king and its towns, and every person in it. He left none remaining, as he had done to Eglon, and devoted it to destruction and every person in it.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Joshua and all Israel with him turned back to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6103AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6103AI\"></sup>Debir and fought against it",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and he captured it with its king and all its towns. And they struck them with the edge of the sword and devoted to destruction every person in it; he left none remaining. Just as he had done to Hebron and to Libnah and its king, so he did to Debir and to its king.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So Joshua struck the whole land, the hill country and the Negeb and the lowland <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6105AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6105AJ\"></sup>and the slopes, and all their kings. He left none remaining, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6105AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6105AK\"></sup>but devoted to destruction all that breathed, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel commanded.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Joshua struck them from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6106AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6106AL\"></sup>Kadesh-barnea as far as Gaza, and all the country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6106AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6106AM\"></sup>Goshen, as far as Gibeon.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And Joshua captured all these kings and their land at one time, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6107AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6107AN\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel fought for Israel.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6108AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6108AO\"></sup>Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>When Jabin, king of Hazor, heard of this, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6109A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6109A\"></sup>sent to Jobab king of Madon, and to the king of Shimron, and to the king of Achshaph,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and to the kings who were in the northern hill country, and in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6110B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6110B\"></sup>Arabah south of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6110C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6110C\"></sup>Chinneroth, and in the lowland, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6110D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6110D\"></sup>in Naphoth-dor on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6110E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6110E\"></sup>west,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>to the Canaanites in the east and the west, the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6111F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6111F\"></sup>Jebusites in the hill country, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6111G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6111G\"></sup>Hivites under <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6111H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6111H\"></sup>Hermon in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6111I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6111I\"></sup>Mizpah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they came out with all their troops, a great horde, in number <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6112J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6112J\"></sup>like the sand that is on the seashore, with very many horses and chariots.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And all these kings joined their forces and came and encamped together at the waters of Merom to fight against Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6114K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6114K\"></sup>“Do not be afraid of them, for tomorrow at this time I will give over all of them, slain, to Israel. You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6114L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6114L\"></sup>hamstring their horses and burn their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6114M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6114M\"></sup>chariots with fire.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joshua and all his warriors came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6115N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6115N\"></sup>suddenly against them by the waters of Merom and fell upon them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into the hand of Israel, who struck them and chased them as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6116O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6116O\"></sup>Great Sidon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6116P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6116P\"></sup>Misrephoth-maim, and eastward as far as the Valley of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6116Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6116Q\"></sup>Mizpeh. And they struck them until he left none remaining.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joshua did to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6117R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6117R\"></sup>just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him: he hamstrung their horses and burned their chariots with fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Joshua turned back at that time and captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6118S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6118S\"></sup>Hazor and struck its king with the sword, for Hazor formerly was the head of all those kingdoms.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And they struck with the sword all who were in it, devoting them to destruction; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6119T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6119T\"></sup>there was none left that breathed. And he burned Hazor with fire.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And all the cities of those kings, and all their kings, Joshua captured, and struck them with the edge of the sword, devoting them to destruction, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6120U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6120U\"></sup>just as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But none of the cities that stood on mounds did Israel burn, except Hazor alone; that Joshua burned.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And all the spoil of these cities and the livestock, the people of Israel took for their plunder. But every person they struck with the edge of the sword until they had destroyed them, and they did not leave any who breathed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6123V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6123V\"></sup>Just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses his servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6123W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6123W\"></sup>so Moses commanded Joshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6123X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6123X\"></sup>and so Joshua did. He left nothing undone of all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Joshua took all that land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6124Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6124Y\"></sup>the hill country and all the Negeb and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6124Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6124Z\"></sup>all the land of Goshen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6124AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6124AA\"></sup>and the lowland <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6124AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6124AB\"></sup>and the Arabah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6124AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6124AC\"></sup>and the hill country of Israel and its lowland",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6125AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6125AD\"></sup>from Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6125AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6125AE\"></sup>Baal-gad in the Valley of Lebanon below <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6125AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6125AF\"></sup>Mount Hermon. And he captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6125AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6125AG\"></sup>all their kings and struck them and put them to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joshua made war <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6126AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6126AH\"></sup>a long time with all those kings.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>There was not a city that made peace with the people of Israel except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6127AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6127AI\"></sup>the Hivites, the inhabitants of Gibeon. They took them all in battle.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For it was the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s doing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6128AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6128AJ\"></sup>to harden their hearts that they should come against Israel in battle, in order that they should be devoted to destruction and should receive no mercy but be destroyed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6128AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6128AK\"></sup>just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Joshua came at that time and cut off <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6129AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6129AL\"></sup>the Anakim from the hill country, from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, and from all the hill country of Judah, and from all the hill country of Israel. Joshua devoted them to destruction with their cities.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>There was none of the Anakim left in the land of the people of Israel. Only in Gaza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6130AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6130AM\"></sup>in Gath, and in Ashdod did some remain.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Joshua took the whole land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6131AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6131AN\"></sup>according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Moses. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6131AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6131AO\"></sup>And Joshua gave it for an inheritance to Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6131AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6131AP\"></sup>according to their tribal allotments. And the land had rest from war."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Now these are the kings of the land whom the people of Israel defeated and took possession of their land beyond the Jordan toward the sunrise, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6132A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6132A\"></sup>the Valley of the Arnon to Mount Hermon, with all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6132B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6132B\"></sup>the Arabah eastward:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6133C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6133C\"></sup>Sihon king of the Amorites who lived at Heshbon and ruled from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6133D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6133D\"></sup>from the middle of the valley as far as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6133E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6133E\"></sup>river Jabbok, the boundary of the Ammonites, that is, half of Gilead,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6134F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6134F\"></sup>the Arabah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6134G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6134G\"></sup>to the Sea of Chinneroth eastward, and in the direction of Beth-jeshimoth, to the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, southward to the foot of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6134H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6134H\"></sup>the slopes of Pisgah;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6135I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6135I\"></sup>Og king of Bashan, one of the remnant of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6135J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6135J\"></sup>the Rephaim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6135K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6135K\"></sup>who lived at Ashtaroth and at Edrei",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and ruled over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6136L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6136L\"></sup>Mount Hermon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6136M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6136M\"></sup>Salecah and all Bashan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6136N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6136N\"></sup>to the boundary of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and over half of Gilead to the boundary of Sihon king of Heshbon.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6137O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6137O\"></sup>Moses, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the people of Israel defeated them. And Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6137P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6137P\"></sup>gave their land for a possession to the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And these are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the people of Israel defeated on the west side of the Jordan, from Baal-gad in the Valley of Lebanon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6138Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6138Q\"></sup>Mount Halak, that rises toward Seir (and Joshua gave their land to the tribes of Israel as a possession <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6138R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6138R\"></sup>according to their allotments,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6139S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6139S\"></sup>in the hill country, in the lowland, in the Arabah, in the slopes, in the wilderness, and in the Negeb, the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6139T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6139T\"></sup>the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites):",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6140U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6140U\"></sup>the king of Jericho, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6140V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6140V\"></sup>the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel, one;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6141W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6141W\"></sup>the king of Jerusalem, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6141X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6141X\"></sup>the king of Hebron, one;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6142Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6142Y\"></sup>the king of Jarmuth, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6142Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6142Z\"></sup>the king of Lachish, one;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6143AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6143AA\"></sup>the king of Eglon, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6143AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6143AB\"></sup>the king of Gezer, one;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6144AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6144AC\"></sup>the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6146AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6146AD\"></sup>the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6147AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6147AE\"></sup>the king of Makkedah, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6147AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6147AF\"></sup>the king of Bethel, one;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6150AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6150AG\"></sup>the king of Madon, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6150AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6150AH\"></sup>the king of Hazor, one;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6151AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6151AI\"></sup>the king of Shimron-meron, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6151AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6151AJ\"></sup>the king of Achshaph, one;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6152AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6152AK\"></sup>the king of Taanach, one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6152AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6152AL\"></sup>the king of Megiddo, one;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6154AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6154AM\"></sup>the king of Dor in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6154AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6154AN\"></sup>Naphath-dor, one; the king of Goiim in Galilee, one;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the king of Tirzah, one: in all, thirty-one kings."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6156A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6156A\"></sup>was old and advanced in years, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “You are old and advanced in years, and there remains yet very much land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6156B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6156B\"></sup>to possess.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6157C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6157C\"></sup>This is the land that yet remains: all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6157D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6157D\"></sup>regions of the Philistines, and all those of the Geshurites",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>(from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6158E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6158E\"></sup>Shihor, which is east of Egypt, northward to the boundary of Ekron, it is counted as Canaanite; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6158F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6158F\"></sup>there are five rulers of the Philistines, those of Gaza, Ashdod, Ashkelon, Gath, and Ekron), and those of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6158G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6158G\"></sup>the Avvim,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>in the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that belongs to the Sidonians, to Aphek, to the boundary of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6159H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6159H\"></sup>the Amorites,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and the land of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6160I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6160I\"></sup>Gebalites, and all Lebanon, toward the sunrise, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6160J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6160J\"></sup>Baal-gad below Mount Hermon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6160K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6160K\"></sup>Lebo-hamath,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>all the inhabitants of the hill country from Lebanon to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6161L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6161L\"></sup>Misrephoth-maim, even all the Sidonians. I myself will drive <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6161M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6161M\"></sup>them out from before the people of Israel. Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6161N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6161N\"></sup>allot the land to Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6161O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6161O\"></sup>for an inheritance, as I have commanded you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6162P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6162P\"></sup>divide this land for an inheritance to the nine tribes and half the tribe of Manasseh.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With the other half of the tribe of Manasseh the Reubenites and the Gadites received their inheritance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6163Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6163Q\"></sup>which Moses gave them, beyond the Jordan eastward, as Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6164R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6164R\"></sup>from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and the city that is in the middle of the valley, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6164S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6164S\"></sup>all the tableland of Medeba as far as Dibon;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6165T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6165T\"></sup>and all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, as far as the boundary of the Ammonites;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Gilead, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6166U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6166U\"></sup>region of the Geshurites and Maacathites, and all Mount Hermon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6166V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6166V\"></sup>all Bashan to Salecah;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6167W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6167W\"></sup>all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and in Edrei (he alone was left of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6167X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6167X\"></sup>the remnant of the Rephaim); <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6167Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6167Y\"></sup>these Moses had struck and driven out.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6168Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6168Z\"></sup>Yet the people of Israel did not drive out the Geshurites or the Maacathites, but Geshur and Maacath dwell in the midst of Israel to this day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6169AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6169AA\"></sup>To the tribe of Levi alone Moses gave no inheritance. The offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel are their inheritance, as he said to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of the people of Reuben according to their clans.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So their territory was from Aroer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6171AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6171AB\"></sup>which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and the city that is in the middle of the valley, and all the tableland by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6171AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6171AC\"></sup>Medeba;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>with Heshbon, and all its cities that are in the tableland; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6172AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6172AD\"></sup>Dibon, and Bamoth-baal, and Beth-baal-meon,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6173AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6173AE\"></sup>and Jahaz, and Kedemoth, and Mephaath,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6174AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6174AF\"></sup>Kiriathaim, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6174AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6174AG\"></sup>Sibmah, and Zereth-shahar on the hill of the valley,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6175AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6175AH\"></sup>Beth-peor, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6175AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6175AI\"></sup>the slopes of Pisgah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6175AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6175AJ\"></sup>Beth-jeshimoth,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6176AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6176AK\"></sup>all the cities of the tableland, and all the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6176AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6176AL\"></sup>whom Moses defeated with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6176AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6176AM\"></sup>the leaders of Midian, Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, the princes of Sihon, who lived in the land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6177AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6177AN\"></sup>Balaam also, the son of Beor, the one who practiced divination, was killed with the sword by the people of Israel among the rest of their slain.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the border of the people of Reuben was the Jordan as a boundary. This was the inheritance of the people of Reuben, according to their clans with their cities and villages.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moses gave an inheritance also to the tribe of Gad, to the people of Gad, according to their clans.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6180AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6180AO\"></sup>Their territory was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and half the land of the Ammonites, to Aroer, which is east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6180AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6180AP\"></sup>Rabbah,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and from Heshbon to Ramath-mizpeh and Betonim, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6181AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6181AQ\"></sup>Mahanaim to the territory of Debir,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and in the valley Beth-haram, Beth-nimrah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6182AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6182AR\"></sup>Succoth, and Zaphon, the rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, having the Jordan as a boundary, to the lower end of the Sea of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6182AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6182AS\"></sup>Chinnereth, eastward beyond the Jordan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This is the inheritance of the people of Gad according to their clans, with their cities and villages.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Moses gave an inheritance to the half-tribe of Manasseh. It was allotted to the half-tribe of the people of Manasseh according to their clans.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Their region extended from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6185AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6185AT\"></sup>Mahanaim, through all Bashan, the whole kingdom of Og king of Bashan, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6185AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6185AU\"></sup>the towns of Jair, which are in Bashan, sixty cities,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and half Gilead, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6186AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6186AV\"></sup>Ashtaroth, and Edrei, the cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan. These were allotted to the people of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6186AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6186AW\"></sup>Machir the son of Manasseh for the half of the people of Machir according to their clans.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the inheritances that Moses distributed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6187AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6187AX\"></sup>in the plains of Moab, beyond the Jordan east of Jericho.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6188AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6188AY\"></sup>But to the tribe of Levi Moses gave no inheritance; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel is their inheritance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6188AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6188AZ\"></sup>just as he said to them."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>These are the inheritances that the people of Israel received in the land of Canaan, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6189A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6189A\"></sup>Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and the heads of the fathers' houses of the tribes of the people of Israel gave them to inherit.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Their inheritance was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6190B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6190B\"></sup>by lot, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded by the hand of Moses for the nine and one-half tribes.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6191C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6191C\"></sup>For Moses had given an inheritance to the two and one-half tribes beyond the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6191D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6191D\"></sup>but to the Levites he gave no inheritance among them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6192E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6192E\"></sup>the people of Joseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim. And no portion was given to the Levites in the land, but only cities to dwell in, with their pasturelands for their livestock and their substance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The people of Israel did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6193F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6193F\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses; they allotted the land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the people of Judah came to Joshua at Gilgal. And Caleb the son of Jephunneh the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6194G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6194G\"></sup>Kenizzite said to him, “You know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6194H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6194H\"></sup>what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses the man of God in Kadesh-barnea concerning you and me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6195I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6195I\"></sup>sent me from Kadesh-barnea to spy out the land, and I brought him word again as it was in my heart.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6196J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6196J\"></sup>my brothers who went up with me made the heart of the people melt; yet I wholly followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Moses swore on that day, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6197K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6197K\"></sup>‘Surely the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6197L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6197L\"></sup>on which your foot has trodden shall be an inheritance for you and your children forever, because you have wholly followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And now, behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kept me alive, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6198M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6198M\"></sup>just as he said, these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6198N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6198N\"></sup>forty-five years since the time that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke this word to Moses, while Israel walked in the wilderness. And now, behold, I am this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6198O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6198O\"></sup>eighty-five years old.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6199P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6199P\"></sup>I am still as strong today as I was in the day that Moses sent me; my strength now is as my strength was then, for war and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6199Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6199Q\"></sup>for going and coming.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So now give me this hill country of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke on that day, for you heard on that day how the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6200R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6200R\"></sup>Anakim were there, with great fortified cities. It may be that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be with me, and I shall drive them out just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6201S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6201S\"></sup>blessed him, and he gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6201T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6201T\"></sup>Hebron to Caleb the son of Jephunneh for an inheritance.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6202U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6202U\"></sup>because he wholly followed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6203V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6203V\"></sup>Now the name of Hebron formerly was Kiriath-arba. (Arba was the greatest man among the Anakim.) <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6203W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6203W\"></sup>And the land had rest from war."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The allotment for the tribe of the people of Judah according to their clans reached southward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6204A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6204A\"></sup>to the boundary of Edom, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6204B\"></sup>the wilderness of Zin at the farthest south.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And their south boundary ran from the end of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6205C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6205C\"></sup>Salt Sea, from the bay that faces southward.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>It goes out southward of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6206D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6206D\"></sup>the ascent of Akrabbim, passes along to Zin, and goes up south of Kadesh-barnea, along by Hezron, up to Addar, turns about to Karka,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>passes along to Azmon, goes out by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6207E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6207E\"></sup>the Brook of Egypt, and comes to its end at the sea. This shall be your south boundary.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the east boundary is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6208F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6208F\"></sup>Salt Sea, to the mouth of the Jordan. And the boundary on the north side runs from the bay of the sea at the mouth of the Jordan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the boundary goes up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6209G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6209G\"></sup>Beth-hoglah and passes along north of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6209H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6209H\"></sup>Beth-arabah. And the boundary goes up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6209I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6209I\"></sup>the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the boundary goes up to Debir from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6210J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6210J\"></sup>the Valley of Achor, and so northward, turning toward Gilgal, which is opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6210K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6210K\"></sup>the ascent of Adummim, which is on the south side of the valley. And the boundary passes along to the waters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6210L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6210L\"></sup>En-shemesh and ends at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6210M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6210M\"></sup>En-rogel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the boundary goes up by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6211N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6211N\"></sup>the Valley of the Son of Hinnom at the southern shoulder of the Jebusite (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6211O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6211O\"></sup>that is, Jerusalem). And the boundary goes up to the top of the mountain that lies over against the Valley of Hinnom, on the west, at the northern end of the Valley <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6211P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6211P\"></sup>of Rephaim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the boundary extends from the top of the mountain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6212Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6212Q\"></sup>to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah, and from there to the cities of Mount Ephron. Then the boundary bends around to Baalah (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6212R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6212R\"></sup>that is, Kiriath-jearim).",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the boundary circles west of Baalah to Mount Seir, passes along to the northern shoulder of Mount Jearim (that is, Chesalon), and goes down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6213S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6213S\"></sup>Beth-shemesh and passes along by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6213T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6213T\"></sup>Timnah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The boundary goes out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6214U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6214U\"></sup>to the shoulder of the hill north of Ekron, then the boundary bends around to Shikkeron and passes along to Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6214V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6214V\"></sup>Baalah and goes out to Jabneel. Then the boundary comes to an end at the sea.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the west boundary was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6215W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6215W\"></sup>the Great Sea with its coastline. This is the boundary around the people of Judah according to their clans.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>According to the commandment of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Joshua, he gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh a portion among the people of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6216X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6216X\"></sup>Kiriath-arba, that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6216Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6216Y\"></sup>Hebron (Arba was the father of Anak).",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6217Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6217Z\"></sup>Sheshai and Ahiman and Talmai, the descendants of Anak.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he went up from there against the inhabitants of Debir. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6218AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6218AA\"></sup>Now the name of Debir formerly was Kiriath-sepher.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Caleb said, “Whoever strikes Kiriath-sepher and captures it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter as wife.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6220AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6220AB\"></sup>And Othniel the son of Kenaz, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6220AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6220AC\"></sup>the brother of Caleb, captured it. And he gave him Achsah his daughter as wife.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field. And she got off her donkey, and Caleb said to her, “What do you want?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She said to him, “Give me a blessing. Since you have given me the land of the Negeb, give me also springs of water.” And he gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Judah according to their clans.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The cities belonging to the tribe of the people of Judah in the extreme south, toward the boundary of Edom, were Kabzeel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6224AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6224AD\"></sup>Eder, Jagur,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6227AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6227AE\"></sup>Ziph, Telem, Bealoth,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Hazor-hadattah, Kerioth-hezron (that is, Hazor),",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Amam, Shema, Moladah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hazar-gaddah, Heshmon, Beth-pelet,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Hazar-shual, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6231AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6231AF\"></sup>Beersheba, Biziothiah,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Baalah, Iim, Ezem,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6234AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6234AG\"></sup>Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: in all, twenty-nine cities with their villages.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And in the lowland, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6236AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6236AH\"></sup>Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Zanoah, En-gannim, Tappuah, Enam,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6238AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6238AI\"></sup>Jarmuth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6238AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6238AJ\"></sup>Adullam, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6238AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6238AK\"></sup>Socoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6238AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6238AL\"></sup>Azekah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Shaaraim, Adithaim, Gederah, Gederothaim: fourteen cities with their villages.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal-gad,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Dilean, Mizpeh, Joktheel,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6242AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6242AM\"></sup>Lachish, Bozkath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6242AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6242AN\"></sup>Eglon,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Cabbon, Lahmam, Chitlish,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Gederoth, Beth-dagon, Naamah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6244AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6244AO\"></sup>Makkedah: sixteen cities with their villages.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6245AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6245AP\"></sup>Libnah, Ether, Ashan,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Iphtah, Ashnah, Nezib,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6247AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6247AQ\"></sup>Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6248AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6248AR\"></sup>Ekron, with its towns and its villages;",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>from Ekron to the sea, all that were by the side of Ashdod, with their villages.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6250AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6250AS\"></sup>Ashdod, its towns and its villages; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6250AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6250AT\"></sup>Gaza, its towns and its villages; to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6250AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6250AU\"></sup>the Brook of Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6250AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6250AV\"></sup>the Great Sea with its coastline.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And in the hill country, Shamir, Jattir, Socoh,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Dannah, Kiriath-sannah (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6252AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6252AW\"></sup>that is, Debir),",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6254AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6254AX\"></sup>Goshen, Holon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6254AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6254AY\"></sup>Giloh: eleven cities with their villages.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Arab, Dumah, Eshan,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Janim, Beth-tappuah, Aphekah,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Humtah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6257AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6257AZ\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6257BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6257BA\"></sup>Hebron), and Zior: nine cities with their villages.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6258BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6258BB\"></sup>Maon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6258BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6258BC\"></sup>Carmel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6258BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6258BD\"></sup>Ziph, Juttah,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah,",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Kain, Gibeah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6260BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6260BE\"></sup>Timnah: ten cities with their villages.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Halhul, Beth-zur, Gedor,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Maarath, Beth-anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6263BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6263BF\"></sup>Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), and Rabbah: two cities with their villages.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>In the wilderness, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6264BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6264BG\"></sup>Beth-arabah, Middin, Secacah,",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Nibshan, the City of Salt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6265BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6265BH\"></sup>Engedi: six cities with their villages.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6266BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6266BI\"></sup>Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6266BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6266BJ\"></sup>the people of Judah could not drive out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6266BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6266BK\"></sup>so the Jebusites dwell with the people of Judah at Jerusalem to this day."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>The allotment of the people of Joseph went from the Jordan by Jericho, east of the waters of Jericho, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6267A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6267A\"></sup>into the wilderness, going up from Jericho into the hill country to Bethel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6268B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6268B\"></sup>going from Bethel to Luz, it passes along to Ataroth, the territory of the Archites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then it goes down westward to the territory of the Japhletites, as far as the territory of Lower <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6269C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6269C\"></sup>Beth-horon, then to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6269D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6269D\"></sup>Gezer, and it ends at the sea.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6270E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6270E\"></sup>The people of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, received their inheritance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The territory of the people of Ephraim by their clans was as follows: the boundary of their inheritance on the east was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6271F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6271F\"></sup>Ataroth-addar as far as Upper Beth-horon,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the boundary goes from there to the sea. On the north is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6272G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6272G\"></sup>Michmethath. Then on the east the boundary turns around toward Taanath-shiloh and passes along beyond it on the east to Janoah,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then it goes down from Janoah to Ataroth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6273H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6273H\"></sup>to Naarah, and touches Jericho, ending at the Jordan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6274I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6274I\"></sup>Tappuah the boundary goes westward to the brook Kanah and ends at the sea. Such is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Ephraim by their clans,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>together with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6275J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6275J\"></sup>the towns that were set apart for the people of Ephraim within the inheritance of the Manassites, all those towns with their villages.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6276K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6276K\"></sup>they did not drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer, so the Canaanites have lived in the midst of Ephraim to this day but have been made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6276L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6276L\"></sup>to do forced labor."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Then allotment was made to the people of Manasseh, for he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6277A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6277A\"></sup>the firstborn of Joseph. To <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6277B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6277B\"></sup>Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6277C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6277C\"></sup>were allotted Gilead and Bashan, because he was a man of war.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And allotments were made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6278D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6278D\"></sup>to the rest of the people of Manasseh by their clans, Abiezer, Helek, Asriel, Shechem, Hepher, and Shemida. These were the male descendants of Manasseh the son of Joseph, by their clans.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6279E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6279E\"></sup>Zelophehad the son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Machir, son of Manasseh, had no sons, but only daughters, and these are the names of his daughters: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6279F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6279F\"></sup>Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They approached <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6280G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6280G\"></sup>Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and the leaders and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6280H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6280H\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses to give us an inheritance along with our brothers.” So according to the mouth of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> he gave them an inheritance among the brothers of their father.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thus there fell to Manasseh ten portions, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6281I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6281I\"></sup>the land of Gilead and Bashan, which is on the other side of the Jordan,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance along with his sons. The land of Gilead was allotted to the rest of the people of Manasseh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The territory of Manasseh reached from Asher to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6283J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6283J\"></sup>Michmethath, which is east of Shechem. Then the boundary goes along southward to the inhabitants of En-tappuah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6284K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6284K\"></sup>Tappuah belonged to Manasseh, but the town of Tappuah on the boundary of Manasseh belonged to the people of Ephraim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6285L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6285L\"></sup>Then the boundary went down to the brook Kanah. These cities, to the south of the brook, among the cities of Manasseh, belong to Ephraim. Then the boundary of Manasseh goes on the north side of the brook and ends at the sea,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the land to the south being Ephraim's and that to the north being Manasseh's, with the sea forming its boundary. On the north Asher is reached, and on the east Issachar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Also in Issachar and in Asher <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6287M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6287M\"></sup>Manasseh had Beth-shean and its villages, and Ibleam and its villages, and the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6287N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6287N\"></sup>Dor and its villages, and the inhabitants of En-dor and its villages, and the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6287O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6287O\"></sup>Taanach and its villages, and the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6287P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6287P\"></sup>Megiddo and its villages; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6287Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6287Q\"></sup>the third is Naphath.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6288R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6288R\"></sup>Yet the people of Manasseh could not take possession of those cities, but the Canaanites persisted in dwelling in that land.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now when the people of Israel grew strong, they put the Canaanites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6289S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6289S\"></sup>to forced labor, but did not utterly drive them out.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6290T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6290T\"></sup>the people of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, “Why have you given me but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6290U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6290U\"></sup>one lot and one portion as an inheritance, although I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6290V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6290V\"></sup>a numerous people, since all along the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed me?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Joshua said to them, “If you are a numerous people, go up by yourselves to the forest, and there clear ground for yourselves in the land of the Perizzites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6291W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6291W\"></sup>the Rephaim, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6291X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6291X\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim is too narrow for you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The people of Joseph said, “The hill country is not enough for us. Yet all the Canaanites who dwell in the plain have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6292Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6292Y\"></sup>chariots of iron, both those in Beth-shean and its villages and those in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6292Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6292Z\"></sup>the Valley of Jezreel.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Joshua said to the house of Joseph, to Ephraim and Manasseh, “You are a numerous people and have great power. You shall not have one allotment only,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>but the hill country shall be yours, for though it is a forest, you shall clear it and possess it to its farthest borders. For you shall drive out the Canaanites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6294AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6294AA\"></sup>though they have chariots of iron, and though they are strong.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Then the whole congregation of the people of Israel assembled at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6295A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6295A\"></sup>Shiloh and set up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6295B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6295B\"></sup>the tent of meeting there. The land lay subdued before them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There remained among the people of Israel seven tribes whose inheritance had not yet been apportioned.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Joshua said to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6297C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6297C\"></sup>“How long will you put off going in to take possession of the land, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, has given you?",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Provide three men from each tribe, and I will send them out that they may set out and go up and down the land. They shall write a description of it with a view to their inheritances, and then come to me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They shall divide it into seven portions. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6299D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6299D\"></sup>Judah shall continue in his territory on the south, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6299E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6299E\"></sup>and the house of Joseph shall continue in their territory on the north.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And you shall describe the land in seven divisions and bring the description here to me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6300F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6300F\"></sup>And I will cast lots for you here before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6301G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6301G\"></sup>The Levites have no portion among you, for the priesthood of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is their heritage. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6301H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6301H\"></sup>And Gad and Reuben and half the tribe of Manasseh have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan eastward, which Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the men arose and went, and Joshua charged those who went to write the description of the land, saying, “Go up and down in the land and write a description and return to me. And I will cast lots for you here before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Shiloh.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the men went and passed up and down in the land and wrote in a book a description of it by towns in seven divisions. Then they came to Joshua to the camp at Shiloh,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6304I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6304I\"></sup>cast lots for them in Shiloh before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And there Joshua apportioned the land to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6304J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6304J\"></sup>to each his portion.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The lot of the tribe of the people of Benjamin according to its clans came up, and the territory allotted to it fell between the people of Judah and the people of Joseph.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6306K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6306K\"></sup>On the north side their boundary began at the Jordan. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6306L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6306L\"></sup>Then the boundary goes up to the shoulder north of Jericho, then up through the hill country westward, and it ends at the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6306M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6306M\"></sup>Beth-aven.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there the boundary passes along southward in the direction of Luz, to the shoulder of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6307N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6307N\"></sup>Luz (that is, Bethel), then the boundary goes down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6307O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6307O\"></sup>Ataroth-addar, on the mountain that lies south of Lower <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6307P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6307P\"></sup>Beth-horon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the boundary goes in another direction, turning on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6308Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6308Q\"></sup>western side southward from the mountain that lies to the south, opposite Beth-horon, and it ends at Kiriath-baal (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6308R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6308R\"></sup>that is, Kiriath-jearim), a city belonging to the people of Judah. This forms the western side.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the southern side begins at the outskirts of Kiriath-jearim. And the boundary goes from there to Ephron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6309S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6309S\"></sup>to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the boundary goes down to the border of the mountain that overlooks <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6310T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6310T\"></sup>the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, which is at the north end of the Valley of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6310U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6310U\"></sup>Rephaim. And it then goes down the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6310V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6310V\"></sup>Valley of Hinnom, south of the shoulder of the Jebusites, and downward to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6310W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6310W\"></sup>En-rogel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then it bends in a northerly direction going on to En-shemesh, and from there goes to Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim. Then it goes down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6311X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6311X\"></sup>the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and passing on to the north of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6312Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6312Y\"></sup>the shoulder of Beth-arabah it goes down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6312Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6312Z\"></sup>the Arabah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the boundary passes on to the north of the shoulder of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6313AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6313AA\"></sup>Beth-hoglah. And the boundary ends at the northern bay of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6313AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6313AB\"></sup>the Salt Sea, at the south end of the Jordan: this is the southern border.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The Jordan forms its boundary on the eastern side. This is the inheritance of the people of Benjamin, according to their clans, boundary by boundary all around.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now the cities of the tribe of the people of Benjamin according to their clans were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6315AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6315AC\"></sup>Jericho, Beth-hoglah, Emek-keziz,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Beth-arabah, Zemaraim, Bethel,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Avvim, Parah, Ophrah,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Chephar-ammoni, Ophni, Geba—twelve cities with their villages:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Gibeon, Ramah, Beeroth,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Mizpeh, Chephirah, Mozah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Zela, Haeleph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6322AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6322AD\"></sup>Jebus (that is, Jerusalem), Gibeah and Kiriath-jearim—fourteen cities with their villages. This is the inheritance of the people of Benjamin according to its clans."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of the people of Simeon, according to their clans, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6323A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6323A\"></sup>and their inheritance was in the midst of the inheritance of the people of Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6324B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6324B\"></sup>And they had for their inheritance Beersheba, Sheba, Moladah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Hazar-shual, Balah, Ezem,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ziklag, Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Beth-lebaoth, and Sharuhen—thirteen cities with their villages;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan—four cities with their villages,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>together with all the villages around these cities as far as Baalath-beer, Ramah of the Negeb. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Simeon according to their clans.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6331C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6331C\"></sup>The inheritance of the people of Simeon formed part of the territory of the people of Judah. Because the portion of the people of Judah was too large for them, the people of Simeon obtained an inheritance in the midst of their inheritance.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The third lot came up for the people of Zebulun, according to their clans. And the territory of their inheritance reached as far as Sarid.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then their boundary goes up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6333D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6333D\"></sup>westward and on to Mareal and touches Dabbesheth, then the brook that is east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6333E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6333E\"></sup>Jokneam.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>From Sarid it goes in the other direction eastward toward the sunrise to the boundary of Chisloth-tabor. From there it goes to Daberath, then up to Japhia.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>From there it passes along on the east toward the sunrise to Gath-hepher, to Eth-kazin, and going on to Rimmon it bends toward Neah,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>then on the north the boundary turns about to Hannathon, and it ends at the Valley of Iphtahel;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and Kattath, Nahalal, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6337F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6337F\"></sup>Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem—twelve cities with their villages.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This is the inheritance of the people of Zebulun, according to their clans—these cities with their villages.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The fourth lot came out for Issachar, for the people of Issachar, according to their clans.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Their territory included Jezreel, Chesulloth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6340G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6340G\"></sup>Shunem,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hapharaim, Shion, Anaharath,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Remeth, En-gannim, En-haddah, Beth-pazzez.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The boundary also touches Tabor, Shahazumah, and Beth-shemesh, and its boundary ends at the Jordan—sixteen cities with their villages.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Issachar, according to their clans—the cities with their villages.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The fifth lot came out for the tribe of the people of Asher according to their clans.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Their territory included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Allammelech, Amad, and Mishal. On the west it touches <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6348H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6348H\"></sup>Carmel and Shihor-libnath,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>then it turns eastward, it goes to Beth-dagon, and touches Zebulun and the Valley of Iphtahel northward to Beth-emek and Neiel. Then it continues in the north to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6349I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6349I\"></sup>Cabul,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, Kanah, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6350J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6350J\"></sup>Sidon the Great.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then the boundary turns to Ramah, reaching to the fortified city of Tyre. Then the boundary turns to Hosah, and it ends at the sea; Mahalab, Achzib,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Ummah, Aphek and Rehob—twenty-two cities with their villages.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Asher according to their clans—these cities with their villages.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The sixth lot came out for the people of Naphtali, for the people of Naphtali, according to their clans.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And their boundary ran from Heleph, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6355K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6355K\"></sup>the oak in Zaanannim, and Adami-nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum, and it ended at the Jordan.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the boundary turns <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6356L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6356L\"></sup>westward to Aznoth-tabor and goes from there to Hukkok, touching Zebulun at the south and Asher on the west and Judah on the east at the Jordan.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6357M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6357M\"></sup>Chinnereth,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Adamah, Ramah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6358N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6358N\"></sup>Hazor,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Kedesh, Edrei, En-hazor,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Yiron, Migdal-el, Horem, Beth-anath, and Beth-shemesh—nineteen cities with their villages.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Naphtali according to their clans—the cities with their villages.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The seventh lot came out for the tribe of the people of Dan, according to their clans.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And the territory of its inheritance included Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir-shemesh,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6364O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6364O\"></sup>Shaalabbin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6364P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6364P\"></sup>Aijalon, Ithlah,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Elon, Timnah, Ekron,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Jehud, Bene-berak, Gath-rimmon,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>and Me-jarkon and Rakkon with the territory over against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6368Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6368Q\"></sup>Joppa.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6369R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6369R\"></sup>the territory of the people of Dan was lost to them, the people of Dan went up and fought against Leshem, and after capturing it and striking it with the sword they took possession of it and settled in it, calling Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their ancestor.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Dan, according to their clans—these cities with their villages.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When they had finished distributing the several territories of the land as inheritances, the people of Israel gave an inheritance among them to Joshua the son of Nun.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>By command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> they gave him the city that he asked, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6372S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6372S\"></sup>Timnath-serah in the hill country of Ephraim. And he rebuilt the city and settled in it.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6373T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6373T\"></sup>These are the inheritances that Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and the heads of the fathers' houses of the tribes of the people of Israel distributed by lot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6373U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6373U\"></sup>at Shiloh before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, at the entrance of the tent of meeting. So they finished dividing the land."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Joshua,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the people of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6375A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6375A\"></sup>‘Appoint the cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>that the manslayer who strikes any person without intent or unknowingly may flee there. They shall be for you a refuge from the avenger of blood.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall flee to one of these cities and shall stand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6377B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6377B\"></sup>at the entrance of the gate of the city and explain his case to the elders of that city. Then they shall take him into the city and give him a place, and he shall remain with them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not give up the manslayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unknowingly, and did not hate him in the past.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he shall remain in that city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6379C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6379C\"></sup>until he has stood before the congregation for judgment, until the death of him who is high priest at the time. Then the manslayer may return to his own town and his own home, to the town from which he fled.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they set apart <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6380D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6380D\"></sup>Kedesh in Galilee in the hill country of Naphtali, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6380E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6380E\"></sup>Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6380F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6380F\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron) <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6380G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6380G\"></sup>in the hill country of Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, they appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6381H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6381H\"></sup>Bezer in the wilderness on the tableland, from the tribe of Reuben, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6381I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6381I\"></sup>Ramoth in Gilead, from the tribe of Gad, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6381J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6381J\"></sup>Golan in Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These were the cities designated for all the people of Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6382K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6382K\"></sup>for the stranger sojourning among them, that anyone who killed a person without intent could flee there, so that he might not die by the hand of the avenger of blood, till he stood before the congregation."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Then the heads of the fathers' houses of the Levites came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6383A\"></sup>to Eleazar the priest and to Joshua the son of Nun and to the heads of the fathers' houses of the tribes of the people of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they said to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6384B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6384B\"></sup>at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6384C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6384C\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses that we be given cities to dwell in, along with their pasturelands for our livestock.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So by command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the people of Israel gave to the Levites the following cities and pasturelands out of their inheritance.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The lot came out for the clans of the Kohathites. So those Levites who were descendants of Aaron the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6386D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6386D\"></sup>received by lot from the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin, thirteen cities.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the rest of the Kohathites received by lot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6387E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6387E\"></sup>from the clans of the tribe of Ephraim, from the tribe of Dan and the half-tribe of Manasseh, ten cities.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6388F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6388F\"></sup>Gershonites received by lot from the clans of the tribe of Issachar, from the tribe of Asher, from the tribe of Naphtali, and from the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6389G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6389G\"></sup>Merarites according to their clans received from the tribe of Reuben, the tribe of Gad, and the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These cities and their pasturelands the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6390H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6390H\"></sup>gave by lot to the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6390I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6390I\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Out of the tribe of the people of Judah and the tribe of the people of Simeon they gave the following cities mentioned by name,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>which went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6392J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6392J\"></sup>the descendants of Aaron, one of the clans of the Kohathites who belonged to the people of Levi; since the lot fell to them first.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6393K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6393K\"></sup>They gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6393L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6393L\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (Arba being the father of Anak), that is Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6393M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6393M\"></sup>in the hill country of Judah, along with the pasturelands around it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the fields of the city and its villages had been given to Caleb the son of Jephunneh as his possession.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And to the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6395N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6395N\"></sup>the city of refuge for the manslayer, with its pasturelands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6395O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6395O\"></sup>Libnah with its pasturelands,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jattir with its pasturelands, Eshtemoa with its pasturelands,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Holon with its pasturelands, Debir with its pasturelands,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Ain with its pasturelands, Juttah with its pasturelands, Beth-shemesh with its pasturelands—nine cities out of these two tribes;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then out of the tribe of Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6399P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6399P\"></sup>Gibeon with its pasturelands, Geba with its pasturelands,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Anathoth with its pasturelands, and Almon with its pasturelands—four cities.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The cities of the descendants of Aaron, the priests, were in all thirteen cities with their pasturelands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6402Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6402Q\"></sup>As to the rest of the Kohathites belonging to the Kohathite clans of the Levites, the cities allotted to them were out of the tribe of Ephraim.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>To them were given Shechem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6403R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6403R\"></sup>the city of refuge for the manslayer, with its pasturelands in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasturelands,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kibzaim with its pasturelands, Beth-horon with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and out of the tribe of Dan, Elteke with its pasturelands, Gibbethon with its pasturelands,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Aijalon with its pasturelands, Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Taanach with its pasturelands, and Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands—two cities.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The cities of the clans of the rest of the Kohathites were ten in all with their pasturelands.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6409S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6409S\"></sup>And to the Gershonites, one of the clans of the Levites, were given out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with its pasturelands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6409T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6409T\"></sup>the city of refuge for the manslayer, and Beeshterah with its pasturelands—two cities;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and out of the tribe of Issachar, Kishion with its pasturelands, Daberath with its pasturelands,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jarmuth with its pasturelands, En-gannim with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and out of the tribe of Asher, Mishal with its pasturelands, Abdon with its pasturelands,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Helkath with its pasturelands, and Rehob with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and out of the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its pasturelands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6414U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6414U\"></sup>the city of refuge for the manslayer, Hammoth-dor with its pasturelands, and Kartan with its pasturelands—three cities.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The cities of the several clans of the Gershonites were in all thirteen cities with their pasturelands.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6416V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6416V\"></sup>And to the rest of the Levites, the Merarite clans, were given out of the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its pasturelands, Kartah with its pasturelands,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Dimnah with its pasturelands, Nahalal with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and out of the tribe of Reuben, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6418W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6418W\"></sup>Bezer with its pasturelands, Jahaz with its pasturelands,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Kedemoth with its pasturelands, and Mephaath with its pasturelands—four cities;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and out of the tribe of Gad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6420X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6420X\"></sup>Ramoth in Gilead with its pasturelands, the city of refuge for the manslayer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6420Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6420Y\"></sup>Mahanaim with its pasturelands,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6421Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6421Z\"></sup>Heshbon with its pasturelands, Jazer with its pasturelands—four cities in all.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>As for the cities of the several Merarite clans, that is, the remainder of the clans of the Levites, those allotted to them were in all twelve cities.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6423AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6423AA\"></sup>The cities of the Levites in the midst of the possession of the people of Israel were in all forty-eight cities with their pasturelands.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>These cities each had its pasturelands around it. So it was with all these cities.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6425AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6425AB\"></sup>Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave to Israel all the land that he swore to give to their fathers. And they took possession of it, and they settled there.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6426AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6426AC\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them rest on every side just as he had sworn to their fathers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6426AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6426AD\"></sup>Not one of all their enemies had withstood them, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6426AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6426AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given all their enemies into their hands.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6427AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6427AF\"></sup>Not one word of all the good promises that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made to the house of Israel had failed; all came to pass."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>At that time Joshua summoned the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and said to them, “You have kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6429A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6429A\"></sup>all that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6429B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6429B\"></sup>and have obeyed my voice in all that I have commanded you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You have not forsaken your brothers these many days, down to this day, but have been careful to keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6431C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6431C\"></sup>And now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given rest to your brothers, as he promised them. Therefore turn and go to your tents in the land where your possession lies, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6431D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6431D\"></sup>which Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave you on the other side of the Jordan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6432E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6432E\"></sup>Only be very careful to observe the commandment and the law that Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6432F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6432F\"></sup>to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and to walk in all his ways and to keep his commandments and to cling to him and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6433G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6433G\"></sup>blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their tents.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now to the one half of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession in Bashan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6434H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6434H\"></sup>but to the other half Joshua had given a possession beside their brothers in the land west of the Jordan. And when Joshua sent them away to their homes and blessed them,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>he said to them, “Go back to your tents with much wealth and with very much livestock, with silver, gold, bronze, and iron, and with much clothing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6435I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6435I\"></sup>Divide the spoil of your enemies with your brothers.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh returned home, parting from the people of Israel at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan, to go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6436J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6436J\"></sup>to the land of Gilead, their own land of which they had possessed themselves by command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And when they came to the region of the Jordan that is in the land of Canaan, the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh built there an altar by the Jordan, an altar of imposing size.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6438K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6438K\"></sup>heard it said, “Behold, the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh have built the altar at the frontier of the land of Canaan, in the region about the Jordan, on the side that belongs to the people of Israel.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And when the people of Israel heard of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6439L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6439L\"></sup>the whole assembly of the people of Israel gathered at Shiloh to make war against them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the people of Israel sent to the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6440M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6440M\"></sup>Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and with him ten chiefs, one from each of the tribal families of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6441N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6441N\"></sup>every one of them the head of a family among the clans of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they came to the people of Reuben, the people of Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, and they said to them,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Thus says the whole congregation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘What is this breach of faith that you have committed against the God of Israel in turning away this day from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by building yourselves an altar this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6443O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6443O\"></sup>in rebellion against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Have we not had enough of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6444P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6444P\"></sup>the sin at Peor from which even yet we have not cleansed ourselves, and for which there came a plague upon the congregation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>that you too must turn away this day from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? And if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6445Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6445Q\"></sup>you too rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> today then tomorrow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6445R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6445R\"></sup>he will be angry with the whole congregation of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But now, if the land of your possession is unclean, pass over into the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6446S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6446S\"></sup>where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s tabernacle stands, and take for yourselves a possession among us. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6446T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6446T\"></sup>Only do not rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> or make us as rebels by building for yourselves an altar other than the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6447U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6447U\"></sup>Did not Achan the son of Zerah break faith in the matter of the devoted things, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6447V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6447V\"></sup>wrath fell upon all the congregation of Israel? And he did not perish alone for his iniquity.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the people of Reuben, the people of Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh said in answer to the heads of the families of Israel,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“The Mighty One, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6449W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6449W\"></sup>God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! The Mighty One, God, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6449X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6449X\"></sup>He knows; and let Israel itself know! If it was in rebellion or in breach of faith against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, do not spare us today",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>for building an altar to turn away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Or if we did so to offer burnt offerings or grain offerings or peace offerings on it, may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6450Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6450Y\"></sup>take vengeance.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>No, but we did it from fear that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6451Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6451Z\"></sup>in time to come your children might say to our children, ‘What have you to do with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made the Jordan a boundary between us and you, you people of Reuben and people of Gad. You have no portion in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’ So your children might make our children cease to worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Therefore we said, ‘Let us now build an altar, not for burnt offering, nor for sacrifice,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>but to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6454AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6454AA\"></sup>a witness between us and you, and between our generations after us, that we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6454AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6454AB\"></sup>do perform the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in his presence with our burnt offerings and sacrifices and peace offerings, so your children will not say to our children in time to come, “You have no portion in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And we thought, ‘If this should be said to us or to our descendants in time to come, we should say, “Behold, the copy of the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which our fathers made, not for burnt offerings, nor for sacrifice, but to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6455AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6455AC\"></sup>a witness between us and you.”’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Far be it from us that we should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6456AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6456AD\"></sup>rebel against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and turn away this day from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6456AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6456AE\"></sup>by building an altar for burnt offering, grain offering, or sacrifice, other than the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God that stands before his tabernacle!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6457AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6457AF\"></sup>Phinehas the priest and the chiefs of the congregation, the heads of the families of Israel who were with him, heard the words that the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the people of Manasseh spoke, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6457AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6457AG\"></sup>it was good in their eyes.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said to the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the people of Manasseh, “Today we know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6458AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6458AH\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is in our midst, because you have not committed this breach of faith against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Now you have delivered the people of Israel from the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, and the chiefs, returned from the people of Reuben and the people of Gad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6459AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6459AI\"></sup>in the land of Gilead to the land of Canaan, to the people of Israel, and brought back word to them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the report <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6460AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6460AJ\"></sup>was good in the eyes of the people of Israel. And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6460AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6460AK\"></sup>blessed God and spoke no more of making war against them to destroy the land where the people of Reuben and the people of Gad were settled.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The people of Reuben and the people of Gad called the altar Witness, “For,” they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6461AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6461AL\"></sup>“it is a witness between us that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>A long time afterward, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6462A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6462A\"></sup>rest to Israel from all their surrounding enemies, and Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6462B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6462B\"></sup>was old and well advanced in years,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6463C\"></sup>summoned all Israel, its elders and heads, its judges and officers, and said to them, “I am now old and well advanced in years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And you have seen all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has done to all these nations for your sake, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6464D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6464D\"></sup>for it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God who has fought for you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6465E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6465E\"></sup>I have allotted to you as an inheritance for your tribes those nations that remain, along with all the nations that I have already cut off, from the Jordan to the Great Sea in the west.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6466F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6466F\"></sup>will push them back before you and drive them out of your sight. And you shall possess their land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6466G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6466G\"></sup>just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God promised you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6467H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6467H\"></sup>be very strong to keep and to do all that is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6467I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6467I\"></sup>turning aside from it neither to the right hand nor to the left,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6468J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6468J\"></sup>that you may not mix with these nations remaining among you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6468K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6468K\"></sup>or make mention of the names of their gods <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6468L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6468L\"></sup>or swear by them or serve them or bow down to them,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6469M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6469M\"></sup>but you shall cling to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God just as you have done to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6470N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6470N\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has driven out before you great and strong nations. And as for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6470O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6470O\"></sup>no man has been able to stand before you to this day.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6471P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6471P\"></sup>One man of you puts to flight a thousand, since it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6471Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6471Q\"></sup>who fights for you, just as he promised you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6472R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6472R\"></sup>Be very careful, therefore, to love the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For if you turn back and cling to the remnant of these nations remaining among you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6473S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6473S\"></sup>and make marriages with them, so that you associate with them and they with you,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>know for certain that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6474T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6474T\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God will no longer drive out these nations before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6474U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6474U\"></sup>but they shall be a snare and a trap for you, a whip on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from off this good ground that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“And now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6475V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6475V\"></sup>I am about to go the way of all the earth, and you know in your hearts and souls, all of you, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6475W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6475W\"></sup>not one word has failed of all the good things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God promised concerning you. All have come to pass for you; not one of them has failed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But just as all the good things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God promised concerning you have been fulfilled for you, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring upon you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6476X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6476X\"></sup>all the evil things, until he has destroyed you from off this good land that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God has given you,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>if you transgress the covenant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, which he commanded you, and go and serve other gods and bow down to them. Then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be kindled against you, and you shall perish quickly from off the good land that he has given to you.”"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6478A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6478A\"></sup>to Shechem and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6478B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6478B\"></sup>summoned the elders, the heads, the judges, and the officers of Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6478C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6478C\"></sup>they presented themselves before God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Joshua said to all the people, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Long ago, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6479D\"></sup>your fathers lived beyond the Euphrates, Terah, the father of Abraham and of Nahor; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6479E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6479E\"></sup>they served other gods.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6480F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6480F\"></sup>Then I took your father Abraham from beyond the River and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6480G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6480G\"></sup>led him through all the land of Canaan, and made his offspring many. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6480H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6480H\"></sup>I gave him Isaac.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And to Isaac I gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6481I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6481I\"></sup>Jacob and Esau. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6481J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6481J\"></sup>And I gave Esau the hill country of Seir to possess, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6481K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6481K\"></sup>but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6482L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6482L\"></sup>And I sent Moses and Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6482M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6482M\"></sup>and I plagued Egypt with what I did in the midst of it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6482N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6482N\"></sup>afterward I brought you out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6483O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6483O\"></sup>I brought your fathers out of Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6483P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6483P\"></sup>you came to the sea. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6483Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6483Q\"></sup>And the Egyptians pursued your fathers with chariots and horsemen to the Red Sea.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6484R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6484R\"></sup>And when they cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6484S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6484S\"></sup>he put darkness between you and the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6484T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6484T\"></sup>and made the sea come upon them and cover them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6484U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6484U\"></sup>and your eyes saw what I did in Egypt. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6484V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6484V\"></sup>And you lived in the wilderness a long time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then I brought you to the land of the Amorites, who lived on the other side of the Jordan. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6485W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6485W\"></sup>They fought with you, and I gave them into your hand, and you took possession of their land, and I destroyed them before you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6486X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6486X\"></sup>Then Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, arose and fought against Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6486Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6486Y\"></sup>And he sent and invited Balaam the son of Beor to curse you,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6487Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6487Z\"></sup>but I would not listen to Balaam. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6487AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6487AA\"></sup>Indeed, he blessed you. So I delivered you out of his hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6488AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6488AB\"></sup>And you went over the Jordan and came to Jericho, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6488AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6488AC\"></sup>and the leaders of Jericho fought against you, and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6488AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6488AD\"></sup>the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. And I gave them into your hand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And I sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6489AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6489AE\"></sup>the hornet before you, which drove them out before you, the two kings of the Amorites; it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6489AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6489AF\"></sup>not by your sword or by your bow.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I gave you a land on which you had not labored <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6490AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6490AG\"></sup>and cities that you had not built, and you dwell in them. You eat the fruit of vineyards and olive orchards that you did not plant.’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6491AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6491AH\"></sup>“Now therefore fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve him in sincerity and in faithfulness. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6491AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6491AI\"></sup>Put away the gods that your fathers served beyond the River and in Egypt, and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6492AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6492AJ\"></sup>And if it is evil in your eyes to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6492AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6492AK\"></sup>choose this day whom you will serve, whether <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6492AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6492AL\"></sup>the gods your fathers served in the region beyond the River, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6492AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6492AM\"></sup>the gods of the Amorites in whose land you dwell. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6492AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6492AN\"></sup>But as for me and my house, we will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the people answered, “Far be it from us that we should forsake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to serve other gods,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>for it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God who brought us and our fathers up from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, and who did those great signs in our sight and preserved us in all the way that we went, and among all the peoples through whom we passed.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> drove out before us all the peoples, the Amorites who lived in the land. Therefore we also will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is our God.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Joshua said to the people, “You are not able to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6496AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6496AO\"></sup>a holy God. He is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6496AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6496AP\"></sup>a jealous God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6496AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6496AQ\"></sup>he will not forgive your transgressions or your sins.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6497AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6497AR\"></sup>If you forsake the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and serve foreign gods, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6497AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6497AS\"></sup>he will turn and do you harm and consume you, after having done you good.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the people said to Joshua, “No, but we will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Joshua said to the people, “You are witnesses against yourselves that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6499AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6499AT\"></sup>you have chosen the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to serve him.” And they said, “We are witnesses.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said, “Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6500AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6500AU\"></sup>put away the foreign gods that are among you, and incline your heart to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the people said to Joshua, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God we will serve, and his voice we will obey.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6502AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6502AV\"></sup>made a covenant with the people that day, and put in place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6502AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6502AW\"></sup>statutes and rules for them at Shechem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6503AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6503AX\"></sup>wrote these words in the Book of the Law of God. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6503AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6503AY\"></sup>he took a large stone and set it up there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6503AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6503AZ\"></sup>under the terebinth that was by the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Joshua said to all the people, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6504BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6504BA\"></sup>this stone shall be a witness against us, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6504BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6504BB\"></sup>it has heard all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he spoke to us. Therefore it shall be a witness against you, lest you deal falsely with your God.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6505BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6505BC\"></sup>sent the people away, every man to his inheritance.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6506BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6506BD\"></sup>After these things Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, died, being 110 years old.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And they buried him in his own inheritance at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6507BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6507BE\"></sup>Timnath-serah, which is in the hill country of Ephraim, north of the mountain of Gaash.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6508BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6508BF\"></sup>Israel served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6508BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6508BG\"></sup>and had known all the work that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did for Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6509BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6509BH\"></sup>As for the bones of Joseph, which the people of Israel brought up from Egypt, they buried them at Shechem, in the piece of land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6509BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6509BI\"></sup>that Jacob bought from the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for a hundred pieces of money. It became an inheritance of the descendants of Joseph.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Eleazar the son of Aaron died, and they buried him at Gibeah, the town of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6510BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6510BJ\"></sup>Phinehas his son, which had been given him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6510BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6510BK\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;